OL,3,CWhat are my rights if my workplace is
OL,4,Ctoo hot?
OL,6,FThe UK has broken records for the
OL,7,Fhottest weather ever seen in May, with
OL,8,FKew Gardens in south-west London
OL,9,Freaching a provisional all-time spring
OL,10,Fhigh of 34.8C on Bank Holiday Monday.
OL,12,FThe Met Office listed 12 locations
OL,13,Fwhere the record was broken, ranging
OL,14,Ffrom Suffolk to Berkshire to
OL,15,FWarwickshire, while 97 of its
OL,16,Fmonitoring sites hit or exceeded 30C.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
