OL,3,CWhat are my rights if my workplace is
OL,4,Ctoo hot?
OL,6,FThe Health and Safety Executive (HSE)
OL,7,Fsets a minimum workplace temperature
OL,8,Fof 16C, or 13C for physically
OL,9,Fdemanding work, but says there is "no
OL,10,Fmeaningful upper limit" because some
OL,11,Findustries regularly operate in high
OL,12,Ftemperatures, such as bakeries and
OL,13,Ffoundries.
OL,15,FEmployers still have a legal duty of
OL,16,Fcare to keep staff safe and must
OL,17,Ffollow health and safety laws,
OL,18,Fincluding:
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
